to the editor paul krugman argues persuasively that alan greenspan has been evasive and disingenuous in denying responsibility for the market bubble of the 90 's column sept 3 but should anyone be surprised mr greenspan is a human being subject to the same frailties as anyone else why should we expect him to be exempt from the universal tendency to rationalize one 's errors and to distort the record to protect one 's self esteem should n't we instead be looking at our own complicity in investing so much power in one man victor a altshul new haven sept 3 2002

